⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Katerina Ivanovna
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦Katerina Ivanovna:BKZ:fc454f⟧

WHO   — Katerina Ivanovna — the lacerated · pride as love
WHAT  — The novel's study of ‘love through pride’: she ruins Dmitri at the trial with a letter, half to save and half to punish, loving and hating in one act.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Dostoevsky anatomises the love that is really wounded vanity — generous and vengeful at once, and finally destructive.
HOW   — By a grand sacrificial gesture that becomes a chain, and testimony that damns the man she cannot decide whether she loves.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I loved him through my pride, which is to say I loved my own sacrifice — and at the trial my wounded vanity helped send him to Siberia.

